<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="11" pageNumber="38">
This genus includes 19 flower-living species in the world (
<bibRefCitation pageId="11" pageNumber="38">ThripsWiki 2013</bibRefCitation>
), of which 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Tenothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenothrips frici" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frici">
<pageBreakToken pageId="12" pageNumber="39" start="start">Tenothrips</pageBreakToken>
frici
</taxonomicName>
(Uzel), is widespread around the world in warm temperate areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Entomology, International" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 487" title="The Thrips of central and south America: An introduction (Insecta: Thysanoptera)." volume="6" year="1996">Mound and Marullo 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirab-balou, M" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Entomology" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="9 - 13" title="A new record for China of Tenothrips frici." volume="3" year="2013">Mirab-balou and Tong 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Bhatti (2003)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed this genus, listing 19 species. Four species are reported from Iran (
<bibRefCitation pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Bhatti et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
), especially on the plant family 
<taxonomicName genus="Asteraceae" lsidName="Asteraceae" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Tenothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenothrips frici" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frici">Tenothrips frici</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in this country.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
